@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Interferium" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, the game requires a 68020(+)
Amiga with Workbench 2.0 or higher.

                             How to play?

  Each game board consists of an area of 8 by 8 spaces, where tiles
that have various patterns are placed on the board. The remaining
spaces are filled with small square dots. These small dots can be
used to make 'paths' between tiles that have the same pattern.

  To create a path between two tiles of the same type, you have to
click on a starting tile and then click on the small dots, one
after an other, until you get to the other tile. When the path you
created is complete, a final path or link will be drawn between
both tiles.

  When creating a path, the next clicked position (whether it is a
tile or a small dot), must always be next to the previously clicked
position, otherwise, the already created 'sub-path' (all clicked
tiles that are 'pressed down') will be eliminated. The same thing
will happen if you click on an already pressed down position, or a
tile that contains a different pattern than the one displayed on
the starting tile.

  No paths can cross another, you have to go around any other path,
as well as any tile that has a different pattern. If you click on
an already made path, all the pressed down positions will return to
their initial state.

  Some game boards have several tiles of the same type, and a tile
with a pattern that have already been linked to another can (or
must) be linked again with another tile... certain paths can even
have a 'closed loop' series of links between tiles...

  You can restart a game board, by clicking on the 'Replay' button,
but note that the number of moves you made will accumulate until
the game board is completed...

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

